g.text: Single crystals suitable for X-ray structural analyses were obtained from
pentane/dichloromethane (9:1). The measurements were performed at 188(2) K with a crystal
mounted on a glass fiber on a Siemens P4 diffractometer (graphite monochromator, Mo-K
= 0.71073 Å). For crystal data and refinement details see the Table 1. The structure
was solved by direct methods using the SHELXTL-97 program package.
